value.name: Utility problems interrupt Greenwood’s Worthsville Road project again
value.description: As Greenwood drivers continue to zig-zag through lane restrictions on Worthsville Road, many have noticed there isn’t any construction happening in the work zone.

value.name: Three remain in critical condition after car accidents
value.description: Three Goulburn Valley residents remain in a critical condition in hospital in Melbourne after two separate car accidents in a week. In the most recent accident, two 16-year-old Shepparton boys were flown to Melbourne's Alfred Hospital after their car lost control in gravel and crashed into a tree on Old Dookie Rd at Pine Lodge about 5.

value.name: Arsenal of weapons found in Cumbria murder accused's room
value.description: This is the collection of weapons police seized from the home of a man accused of "luring" Jordan Watson to his death.

value.name: Barooga suffers narrow loss, Cobram enjoys week off
value.description: Barooga suffered a heart-breaking defeat to Numurkah at the weekend in the Murray Football League. Numurkah notched its third win of the season with a 13.8 (86) to 11.14 (80) triumph.
